      <Notes><![CDATA[  A collaborative research agreement between the Peoples' Republic of China's (PRC) Chinese Academy of Sciences and the United States Department of Energy, signed in August of 1987, has resulted in the compilation and exchange of several data sets that will be useful in reconstructing past climates in China, extending and calibrating instrumental records, and addressing potential CO2-induced global and regional warming.
<br><br>
  This report describes one of the twelve PRC proxy data sets exchanged as part of this bilateral agreement.  These two data files contain annual totals of the number of Chinese counties affected by drought and flood.  Values range from 0-308 counties for drought and 0-123 counties for flooding.  These records may be used to examine long-term occurrences of drought and flooding in China and may be used to verify precipitation, temperature, and dryness/wetness indices and instrumental records.]]></Notes>
